        "content": "<p>A Markov category is an affine monoidal category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>⊗</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(\\mathbf C, 1, \\otimes)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊗</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> such that every object <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> has an assigned comonoid structure <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">y</mi></mrow><mi>X</mi></msub><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>X</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(\\mathsf{copy}_X, !_X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">copy</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.23419099999999995em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4558600000000004em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.24414em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span><br>\nWhat kind of datum is this assignment? Is it a section of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Comon}(\\mathbf C) \\to \\mathbf C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Comon</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68611em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span></span></span></span>? Or would that imply naturality of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{copy}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.63888em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">copy</span></span></span></span></span>, which we reject in order to not degenerate into cartesianity?</p>",
        "id": 258003803,
